Package: fhircrackr
Type: Package
Title: Handling HL7 FHIR resources in R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Thomas", "Peschel", email = "tpeschel@imise.uni-leipzig.de", role = c("aut","cre")),
    person("Jens", "Przybilla", email = "jprzybilla@imise.uni-leipzig.de", role = "aut"),
    person("Julia", "Gantner", email = "julia.gantner@med.uni-jena.de", role = "aut"),
    person("Frank", "Meineke", email = "'frank.meineke@imise.uni-leipzig.de", role = "aut"))
Description: fhiR is a package that conveniently downloads fhir resources in xml format 
    and converts them to R data frames. It uses fhir-search to download bundles 
    from a fhir server, provides functions to save and read xml-files containing such bundles 
    and allows flattening the bundles to data.frames using XPath expressions.
BugReports: https://github.com/POLAR-fhiR/fhircrackr/issues
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
Imports: 
    xml2,
    stringr,
    httr,
    utils
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10)
